member.summary:
Rethrow the Exception while preserving the previous throw location. The following string is inserted in the stack trace to indicate the restore point: "End of stack trace from the previous location where the exception was thrown". This is similar to the way inner exceptions or marshaled exceptions are indicated in stack traces.
This method always throws an exception. It has a return value in order to write calling code like below so that the compiler also knows the code doesn't continue after this call:
throw exception.Rethrow();

member.example:
Sample showing how to populate the EntityPath in connectionString 
           var connectionStringBuilder = new ServiceBusConnectionStringBuilder(connectionString);
           connectionStringBuilder.EntityPath = eventHubDescription.Path;

           var eventHubClient = EventHubClient.CreateFromConnectionString(connectionStringBuilder.ToString());

